A destination wedding is the ultimate romantic gesture — you and everyone you love, gathered somewhere breathtaking. But behind every effortless celebration is a mountain of coordination. After a decade of designing weddings from Udaipur to Bali, here is how we keep it magical instead of maddening.

## Start With the Feeling, Not the Place

Before you fall in love with a venue, decide how you want your wedding to *feel*. Intimate and barefoot on the sand? Regal and grand beneath palace arches? The emotion narrows your destination faster than any Pinterest board.

## Give Your Guests Runway

For a destination wedding, send save-the-dates **8 to 10 months** in advance. Your guests are booking flights and taking time off — generosity with timing is generosity with their experience.

> The couples who relax on their wedding day are the ones who delegated early and trusted their planner completely.

## Build a Realistic Budget

Destination weddings carry costs your hometown wedding never will:

- Travel and accommodation for your core team
- Guest transfers and welcome experiences
- Marriage documentation and permits
- Weather contingency and backup venues

A transparent budget from day one prevents every unwelcome surprise later.

## Lean on Local Expertise

The single biggest predictor of a smooth destination wedding is a planner with **trusted vendors on the ground**. Local relationships mean better pricing, reliable execution and a safety net when the unexpected happens.

## Let Yourself Be a Guest

The whole point is presence. When the logistics are handled by a team you trust, you get to do the one thing that matters — be fully, joyfully in the moment. That is the luxury we design for.

